TITLE: Implementing a Dice Game with Randomness in Sui Move
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a dice game implementation using randomness. It includes a play_dice function that generates a random number and compares it to the player's guess.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/guides/developer/advanced/randomness-onchain.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
module games::dice {
  ...
  public enum Ticket has drop {
    Lost,
    Won,
  }

  public fun is_winner(t: &Ticket): bool {
    match (t) {
      Ticket::Won => true,
      Ticket::Lost => false,
    }
  }

  /// If you guess correctly the output, then you get a GuessedCorrectly object.
  /// Otherwise you get nothing.
  public fun play_dice(guess: u8, fee: Coin<SUI>, r: &Random, ctx: &mut TxContext): Ticket {
    // Pay for the turn
    assert!(coin::value(&fee) == 1000000, EInvalidAmount);
    transfer::public_transfer(fee, CREATOR_ADDRESS);

    // Roll the dice
    let mut generator = new_generator(r, ctx);
    if (guess == generator.generate_u8_in_range(1, 6)) {
      Ticket::Won
    } else {
      Ticket::Lost
    }
  }
  ...
}
```

