TITLE: Removing Element from Vector in Move
DESCRIPTION: This function removes the element at the specified index from the vector, shifting all subsequent elements. It preserves the order of elements but has O(n) complexity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun remove<Element>(v: &mut vector<Element>, mut i: u64): Element {
    let mut len = v.length();
    // i out of bounds; abort
    if (i >= len) abort EINDEX_OUT_OF_BOUNDS;
    len = len - 1;
    while (i < len) {
        v.swap(i, { i = i + 1; i });
    };
    v.pop_back()
}
```

