TITLE: Executing a Swap with Owned Objects in Sui Move
DESCRIPTION: Function to execute a swap between two escrow requests. The custodian matches the two requests, verifies they form a valid swap pair, and transfers each object to its intended recipient. This implementation uses only owned objects without shared objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/guides/developer/sui-101/shared-owned.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public entry fun swap<T: key + store, U: key + store>(
        escrow1: Escrow<T>,
        escrow2: Escrow<U>,
        ctx: &mut TxContext,
    ) {
        let Escrow { id: id1, sender: sender1, recipient: recipient1, exchange_key_id: exchange_key_id1, obj: obj1 } = escrow1;
        let Escrow { id: id2, sender: sender2, recipient: recipient2, exchange_key_id: exchange_key_id2, obj: obj2 } = escrow2;
        object::delete(id1);
        object::delete(id2);

        // Check that the senders/recipients match
        assert!(sender1 == recipient2, ERecipientMismatch);
        assert!(sender2 == recipient1, ESenderMismatch);

        // Check the objects match by comparing key IDs
        let key1 = object::id_from_address(object::id_address(&obj1));
        let key2 = object::id_from_address(object::id_address(&obj2));

        assert!(key2 == exchange_key_id1, EWrongObject);
        assert!(key1 == exchange_key_id2, EWrongObject);

        // Send each object to its new owner
        transfer::transfer(obj1, recipient1);
        transfer::transfer(obj2, recipient2);
    }
```

