/// Create a pool permissionlessly. Any user can create a pool if the pool does not exist.
/// A pool is identified by the pair of coins, <BaseType, QuoteType>.
/// Here, BaseType refers to the asset being traded, and QuoteType refers to the asset used to quote the prices.
/// For example, in a BTC/USDC pool, BTC is the base asset and USDC is the quote asset.
/// @param _DEEP Access to the protocol object that ensures authorization to access certain admin APIs.
/// @param base_type The base asset type. For example, in a BTC/USDC pool, this is BTC.
/// @param quote_type The quote asset type. For example, in a BTC/USDC pool, this is USDC.
/// @param tick_size The tick size (minimum price increment) of the pool, in terms of the number of quote asset's smallest unit.
/// For instance, if USDC has 6 decimals and the tick size is set to 1000, the minimum price increment is 0.001 USDC.
/// @param lot_size The lot size (minimum quantity increment) of the pool, in terms of the number of base asset's smallest unit.
/// For instance, if BTC has 8 decimals and the lot size is set to 1000, the minimum quantity increment is 0.00001 BTC.
/// @param min_size The minimum order size allowed, in terms of the number of base asset's smallest unit.
/// @param creation_fee The fee to create a pool, denominated in DEEP token. This fee is burned.
/// @return pool_id The ID of the created pool.
public fun create_permissionless_pool<BaseType, QuoteType>(
    _DEEP: &DEEP,
    base_type: TypeName,
    quote_type: TypeName,
    tick_size: u64,
    lot_size: u64,
    min_size: u64,
    creation_fee: Coin<DEEPV2>,
    ctx: &mut TxContext
): ID {
    create_pool(base_type, quote_type, tick_size, lot_size, min_size, OWNER_CAP_DEFAULT, creation_fee, ctx)
}
```

