TITLE: Swapping Elements in TableVec in Move
DESCRIPTION: The `swap` function swaps the elements at indices `i` and `j` in TableVec `t`. It checks for out-of-bounds indices and safely performs the swap if indices are valid.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/table_vec.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun swap<Element: store>(t: &mut sui::table_vec::TableVec<Element>, i: u64, j: u64) {
    assert!(t.length() > i, EIndexOutOfBound);
    assert!(t.length() > j, EIndexOutOfBound);
    if (i == j) {
        return
    };
    let element_i = t.contents.remove(i);
    let element_j = t.contents.remove(j);
    t.contents.add(j, element_i);
    t.contents.add(i, element_j);
}
```

