TITLE: Creating a VecMap from Keys and Values Vectors in Move
DESCRIPTION: Constructs a new VecMap from two vectors containing keys and values. Associates elements by their index positions in the vectors. Preserves insertion order and verifies vectors have equal length.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/vec_map.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun from_keys_values<K: copy, V>(mut keys: vector<K>, mut values: vector<V>): VecMap<K, V> {
    assert!(keys.length() == values.length(), EUnequalLengths);
    keys.reverse();
    values.reverse();
    let mut map = empty();
    while (keys.length() != 0) map.insert(keys.pop_back(), values.pop_back());
    keys.destroy_empty();
    values.destroy_empty();
    map
}
```

