TITLE: Initializing GEM Currency in Move using Sui Closed-Loop Token Standard
DESCRIPTION: This function initializes the GEM currency using the Sui Closed-Loop Token standard. It creates the currency, sets policies, freezes metadata, and transfers policy capability to the package publisher.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/guides/developer/coin/in-game-token.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
fun init(witness: GEMS, ctx: &mut TxContext) {
    let (treasury, metadata) = coin::create_currency(
        witness,
        9,
        b"GEM",
        b"Gem",
        b"Game currency, used to create swords",
        option::none(),
        ctx
    );
    transfer::public_transfer(treasury, tx_context::sender(ctx));
    let (_, policy_cap) = transfer_policy::new<GEM>(&metadata, ctx);
    transfer_policy::add_rule(
        &policy_cap,
        transfer_policy::default_rules::royalty_rule<GEM, GEMS>(),
        ctx
    );
    transfer_policy::add_to_balance<GEM, GEMS>(
        &policy_cap,
        balance::zero()
    );
    let pub = package::claim(ctx);
    coin::mint_and_transfer(&mut metadata, GEM_AMOUNT_SMALL, package::publisher_address(&pub), ctx);
    coin::mint_and_transfer(&mut metadata, GEM_AMOUNT_MEDIUM, package::publisher_address(&pub), ctx);
    coin::mint_and_transfer(&mut metadata, GEM_AMOUNT_LARGE, package::publisher_address(&pub), ctx);
    transfer::public_freeze_object(metadata);
    transfer::public_transfer(policy_cap, package::publisher_address(&pub));
    package::burn_publisher(pub);
}
```

