TITLE: Popping Maximum Element from Priority Queue in Move
DESCRIPTION: Function to remove and return the highest priority element from the queue. It swaps the root with the last element, removes the last element, and then restores the max heap property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/priority_queue.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun pop_max<T: drop>(pq: &mut PriorityQueue<T>): (u64, T) {
    let len = pq.entries.length();
    assert!(len > 0, EPopFromEmptyHeap);
    let Entry { priority, value } = pq.entries.swap_remove(0);
    max_heapify_recursive(&mut pq.entries, len - 1, 0);
    (priority, value)
}
```

