TITLE: Emitting Lock Events in a Move Function
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to implement a lock function that emits an event when called. The function creates and emits a LockEvent containing information about the locked object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/guides/developer/sui-101/using-events.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
/// Lock an object inside a wrapper
public fun lock<T: key + store>(obj: T, ctx: &mut TxContext): Lock<T> {
    let sender = tx_context::sender(ctx);
    let id = object::new(ctx);

    // Create and emit a LockEvent containing info
    // about the lock operation
    event::emit(LockEvent<T> {
        locker: sender,
        object_id: object::id(&obj),
        locked_at_ms: tx_context::epoch_timestamp_ms(ctx),
    });

    Lock {
        id,
        obj: option::some(obj)
    }
}
```

