TITLE: Implementing Exclusive Range Iteration Macro in Move
DESCRIPTION: A macro that iterates over a range of values from start (inclusive) to stop (exclusive) and applies a function to each value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/macros.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public macro fun range_do<$T, $R: drop>($start: $T, $stop: $T, $f: |$T| -> $R) {
    let mut i = $start;
    let stop = $stop;
    while (i < stop) {
        $f(i);
        i = i + 1;
    }
}
