TITLE: Dividing Coin into Multiple Equal Parts in Move
DESCRIPTION: Splits a Coin into n-1 new Coins with equal balances, leaving the remainder in the original Coin. This function returns a vector of newly created Coins.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/coin.md#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun divide_into_n<T>(self: &mut Coin<T>, n: u64, ctx: &mut TxContext): vector<Coin<T>> {
    assert!(n > 0, EInvalidArg);
    assert!(n <= value(self), ENotEnough);
    let mut vec = vector[];
    let mut i = 0;
    let split_amount = value(self) / n;
    while (i < n - 1) {
        vec.push_back(self.split(split_amount, ctx));
        i = i + 1;
    };
    vec
}
```

