TITLE: Converting VecMap to Keys and Values Vectors in Move
DESCRIPTION: Unpacks a VecMap into separate vectors for keys and values. The output maintains insertion order, not sorted by key. Reverses the internal vector to preserve original insertion order.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/vec_map.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun into_keys_values<K: copy, V>(self: VecMap<K, V>): (vector<K>, vector<V>) {
    let VecMap { mut contents } = self;
    // reverse the vector so the output keys and values will appear in insertion order
    contents.reverse();
    let mut i = 0;
    let n = contents.length();
    let mut keys = vector[];
    let mut values = vector[];
    while (i < n) {
        let Entry { key, value } = contents.pop_back();
        keys.push_back(key);
        values.push_back(value);
        i = i + 1;
    };
    contents.destroy_empty();
    (keys, values)
}
```

