TITLE: Multiplying U64 by FixedPoint32
DESCRIPTION: Multiplies a u64 integer by a fixed-point number, handling the scale conversion and checking for overflow conditions. The result is truncated to remove any fractional part.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/fixed_point32.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun multiply_u64(val: u64, multiplier: FixedPoint32): u64 {
    // The product of two 64 bit values has 128 bits, so perform the
    // multiplication with u128 types and keep the full 128 bit product
    // to avoid losing accuracy.
    let unscaled_product = val as u128 * (multiplier.value as u128);
    // The unscaled product has 32 fractional bits (from the multiplier)
    // so rescale it by shifting away the low bits.
    let product = unscaled_product >> 32;
    // Check whether the value is too large.
    assert!(product <= MAX_U64, EMULTIPLICATION);
    product as u64
}
```

