TITLE: Checking Current Epoch Deny List Status (Move)
DESCRIPTION: Package-scoped function to check if an address is currently in the deny list. Returns boolean indicating presence in current epoch configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/deny_list.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public(package) fun v2_contains_current_epoch(
    deny_list: &DenyList,
    per_type_index: u64,
    per_type_key: vector<u8>,
    addr: address,
    ctx: &TxContext,
): bool {
    if (!deny_list.per_type_exists(per_type_index, per_type_key)) return false;
    let per_type_config = deny_list.borrow_per_type_config(per_type_index, per_type_key);
    let setting_name = AddressKey(addr);
    config::read_setting(object::id(per_type_config), setting_name, ctx).destroy_or!(false)
}
```

