TITLE: Efficient Element Removal from Vector in Move
DESCRIPTION: This function removes an element from the vector by swapping it with the last element and then popping. It's O(1) but doesn't preserve element order.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun swap_remove<Element>(v: &mut vector<Element>, i: u64): Element {
    assert!(v.length() != 0, EINDEX_OUT_OF_BOUNDS);
    let last_idx = v.length() - 1;
    v.swap(i, last_idx);
    v.pop_back()
}
```

