TITLE: Finding a Value in a Vector Using While Loop and Break in Move
DESCRIPTION: A function that searches for a target value in a vector and returns its position if found. The function uses a while loop with a break statement to exit early when the target is found.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/documentation/book/src/control-flow/loops.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun find_position(values: &vector<u64>, target_value: u64): Option<u64> {
    let size = vector::length(values);
    let mut i = 0;
    let mut found = false;

    while (i < size) {
        if (vector::borrow(values, i) == &target_value) {
            found = true;
            break
        };
        i = i + 1
    };

    if (found) {
        Option::Some(i)
    } else {
        Option::None
    }
}
```

