TITLE: Creating Fixed-Point Value from Rational (Move)
DESCRIPTION: Creates a fixed-point value from a rational number specified by its numerator and denominator. It handles scaling, division, and range checking to ensure the result is within the valid fixed-point range.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/fixed_point32.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun create_from_rational(numerator: u64, denominator: u64): FixedPoint32 {
    let scaled_numerator = numerator as u128 << 64;
    let scaled_denominator = denominator as u128 << 32;
    assert!(scaled_denominator != 0, EDENOMINATOR);
    let quotient = scaled_numerator / scaled_denominator;
    assert!(quotient != 0 || numerator == 0, ERATIO_OUT_OF_RANGE);
    assert!(quotient <= MAX_U64, ERATIO_OUT_OF_RANGE);
    FixedPoint32 { value: quotient as u64 }
}
```

