TITLE: Returning Quote Assets from Flash Loan in DeepBook (Move)
DESCRIPTION: This function handles the return of borrowed quote assets to the Pool. Similar to returning base assets, the FlashLoan object is unwrapped only if the correct amount of assets are returned, otherwise the transaction fails.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/standards/deepbookv3/flash-loans.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun return_flashloan_quote<BaseAsset, QuoteAsset>(pool: &mut Pool<BaseAsset, QuoteAsset>, loan: FlashLoan<QuoteAsset>, coin: Coin<QuoteAsset>) {
    // Emit event
    event::emit(FlashLoanReturnEvent<QuoteAsset, BaseAsset> {
        pool_id: *object::id(pool),
        amount: loan.amount,
    });

    let pool_id = *object::id(pool);
    assert!(pool_id == loan.pool_id, EWrongPool);
    let FlashLoan {pool_id: _, amount} = loan;
    assert!(coin::value(&coin) >= amount, EInsufficientAmount);

    let coin_balance = coin::into_balance(coin);
    balance::join(&mut pool.quote, coin_balance);
}
```

