TITLE: Deserializing Multiple Values from BCS-encoded Bytes in Move
DESCRIPTION: This function demonstrates how to use the sui::bcs module to deserialize multiple values (u8 and u64) from BCS-encoded bytes. It creates a BCS struct from input bytes, peels values sequentially, and returns the extracted values along with remaining bytes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/bcs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
/// This function reads u8 and u64 value from the input
/// and returns the rest of the bytes.
fun deserialize(bytes: vector<u8>): (u8, u64, vector<u8>) {
use sui::bcs::{Self, BCS};

let prepared: BCS = bcs::new(bytes);
let (u8_value, u64_value) = (
prepared.peel_u8(),
prepared.peel_u64()
);

// unpack bcs struct
let leftovers = prepared.into_remainder_bytes();

(u8_value, u64_value, leftovers)
}
```

