TITLE: Generating uint in range with bias control - Move
DESCRIPTION: This macro generates a random unsigned integer within a given range [min, max] using a specified number of bytes for bias control. Preconditions must ensure min is less than or equal to max. It returns a random value within the range, with a bias limited by the num_of_bytes parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/random.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
macro fun uint_in_range<$T: drop>($g: &mut sui::random::RandomGenerator, $min: $T, $max: $T, $num_of_bytes: u8): $T {
    let min = $min;
    let max = $max;
    assert!(min <= max, EInvalidRange);
    if (min == max) return min;
    let range_size = (max - min) as u256 + 1;
    let rand = uint_from_bytes!($g, $num_of_bytes);
    min + (rand % range_size as $T)
}
```

