TITLE: Inserting Element into Vector in Move
DESCRIPTION: This function inserts an element at the specified index in the vector, shifting existing elements if necessary. It preserves order but has O(n) complexity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun insert<Element>(v: &mut vector<Element>, e: Element, mut i: u64) {
    let len = v.length();
    // i too big abort
    if (i > len) abort EINDEX_OUT_OF_BOUNDS;
    v.push_back(e);
    while (i < len) {
        v.swap(i, len);
        i = i + 1
    }
}
```

