TITLE: Folding a Vector into Single Value in Sui Move
DESCRIPTION: A macro function that reduces a vector to a single value by applying a provided function to each element. Similar to fold_left in Rust and reduce in Python and JavaScript, it accumulates a result by processing elements in order.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: Sui Move
CODE:
```
public macro fun fold<$T, $Acc>($v: vector<$T>, $init: $Acc, $f: |$Acc, $T| -> $Acc): $Acc {
    let v = $v;
    let mut acc = $init;
    v.do!(|e| acc = $f(acc, e));
    acc
}
```

