TITLE: Implementing range_do Macro in Move
DESCRIPTION: A macro function that iterates from a start value (inclusive) to a stop value (exclusive) and applies a function to each value in the range.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/macros.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public macro fun range_do<$T, $R: drop>($start: $T, $stop: $T, $f: |$T| -> $R) {
    let mut i = $start;
    let stop = $stop;
    while (i < stop) {
        $f(i);
        i = i + 1;
    }
}
```

