TITLE: Finding a Value in a Vector Using Loop with Break and Return Value in Move
DESCRIPTION: A function that searches for a target value in a vector using a loop expression. It returns the position immediately using break with a value if found, or None if not found.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/documentation/book/src/control-flow/loops.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun find_position(values: &vector<u64>, target_value: u64): Option<u64> {
    let size = vector::length(values);
    let mut i = 0;

    loop {
        if (vector::borrow(values, i) == &target_value) {
            break Option::Some(i)
        } else if (i >= size) {
            break Option::None
        };
        i = i + 1;
    }
}
```

