TITLE: Serializing BridgeMessage in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Serializes a BridgeMessage struct into a vector of bytes. It includes message type, version, sequence number, source chain, and payload.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/bridge/message.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
public fun serialize_message(message: BridgeMessage): vector<u8> {
    let BridgeMessage {
        message_type,
        message_version,
        seq_num,
        source_chain,
        payload
    } = message;
    let mut message = vector[
        message_type,
        message_version,
    ];
    // bcs serializes u64 as 8 bytes
    message.append(reverse_bytes(bcs::to_bytes(&seq_num)));
    message.push_back(source_chain);
    message.append(payload);
    message
}
```

