TITLE: Getting Closest Leaf Index by Key in Move Critbit Tree
DESCRIPTION: The 'get_closest_leaf_index_by_key' function retrieves the index of the closest leaf in a critbit tree for a given key. By traversing the tree based on bitwise operations, it determines the closest node. The function requires the key as a 64-bit unsigned integer and returns a corresponding index or partition index if the tree is empty.
