TITLE: Implementing Vector Length Peeling in Move
DESCRIPTION: Function to read ULEB-encoded vector length from BCS-serialized bytes. Implements ULEB128 decoding for vector lengths.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/bcs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun peel_vec_length(bcs: &mut BCS): u64 {
    let (mut total, mut shift, mut len) = (0u64, 0, 0);
    loop {
        assert!(len <= 4, ELenOutOfRange);
        let byte = bcs.bytes.pop_back() as u64;
        len = len + 1;
        total = total | ((byte & 0x7f) << shift);
        if ((byte & 0x80) == 0) break;
        shift = shift + 7;
    };
    total
}
```

