TITLE: Inserting String at Specific Index in Move
DESCRIPTION: Inserts a string at a specific byte index in another string. The index must be at a valid UTF-8 character boundary.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/string.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun insert(s: &mut String, at: u64, o: String) {
    let bytes = &s.bytes;
    assert!(at <= bytes.length() && internal_is_char_boundary(bytes, at), EInvalidIndex);
    let l = s.length();
    let mut front = s.substring(0, at);
    let end = s.substring(at, l);
    front.append(o);
    front.append(end);
    *s = front;
}
```

