TITLE: Finding Index of Substring in Move
DESCRIPTION: This function finds the index of the first occurrence of a substring within a string. It returns the index of the substring or the length of the string if the substring is not found. It returns 0 if the substring is empty.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/ascii.md#2025-04-22_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
<b>public</b> <b>fun</b> <a href="../std/ascii.md#std_ascii_index_of">index_of</a>(<a href="../std/string.md#std_string">string</a>: &<a href="../std/ascii.md#std_ascii_String">String</a>, substr: &<a href="../std/ascii.md#std_ascii_String">String</a>): <a href="../std/u64.md#std_u64">u64</a> {
    <b>let</b> <b>mut</b> i = 0;
    <b>let</b> (n, m) = (<a href="../std/string.md#std_string">string</a>.<a href="../std/ascii.md#std_ascii_length">length</a>(), substr.<a href="../std/ascii.md#std_ascii_length">length</a>());
    <b>if</b> (n &lt; m) <b>return</b> n;
    <b>while</b> (i &lt;= n - m) {
        <b>let</b> <b>mut</b> j = 0;
        <b>while</b> (j &lt; m && <a href="../std/string.md#std_string">string</a>.bytes[i + j] == substr.bytes[j]) j = j + 1;
        <b>if</b> (j == m) <b>return</b> i;
        i = i + 1;
    };
    n
}
```

