TITLE: Finding Substring Index in ASCII String in Move
DESCRIPTION: This function computes the index of the first occurrence of a substring within an ASCII string. It returns the length of the string if the substring is not found, and 0 if the substring is empty.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/ascii.md#2025-04-22_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun index_of(string: &String, substr: &String): u64 {
    let mut i = 0;
    let (n, m) = (string.length(), substr.length());
    if (n < m) return n;
    while (i <= n - m) {
        let mut j = 0;
        while (j < m && string.bytes[i + j] == substr.bytes[j]) j = j + 1;
        if (j == m) return i;
        i = i + 1;
    };
    n
}
```

