TITLE: Decoding Hex String to Bytes in Move
DESCRIPTION: This function decodes a hexadecimal string into a vector of bytes. It validates the input length and character set, supporting both uppercase and lowercase hex characters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/hex.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun decode(hex: vector<u8>): vector<u8> {
    let (mut i, mut r, l) = (0, vector[], hex.length());
    assert!(l % 2 == 0, EInvalidHexLength);
    while (i < l) {
        let decimal = decode_byte(hex[i]) * 16 + decode_byte(hex[i + 1]);
        r.push_back(decimal);
        i = i + 2;
    };
    r
}
```

