TITLE: Extracting Module Name from TypeName in Rust
DESCRIPTION: The get_module function extracts the module name from a TypeName object. It aborts if given a primitive type. The function parses the TypeName string, skipping the address part and extracting the module name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/type_name.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
public fun get_module(self: &TypeName): String {
    assert!(!self.is_primitive(), ENonModuleType);
    // Starts after address and a double colon: `<addr as HEX>::`
    let mut i = address::length() * 2 + 2;
    let str_bytes = self.name.as_bytes();
    let mut module_name = vector[];
    let colon = ASCII_COLON;
    loop {
        let char = &str_bytes[i];
        if (char != &colon) {
            module_name.push_back(*char);
            i = i + 1;
        } else {
            break
        }
    };
    ascii::string(module_name)
}
```

