TITLE: Returning Base Assets from Flash Loan in DeepBook (Move)
DESCRIPTION: This function handles the return of borrowed base assets to the Pool. The FlashLoan object is unwrapped only if the correct amount of assets are returned, otherwise the transaction fails.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/standards/deepbookv3/flash-loans.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun return_flashloan_base<BaseAsset, QuoteAsset>(pool: &mut Pool<BaseAsset, QuoteAsset>, loan: FlashLoan<BaseAsset>, coin: Coin<BaseAsset>) {
    // Emit event
    event::emit(FlashLoanReturnEvent<BaseAsset, QuoteAsset> {
        pool_id: *object::id(pool),
        amount: loan.amount,
    });

    let pool_id = *object::id(pool);
    assert!(pool_id == loan.pool_id, EWrongPool);
    let FlashLoan {pool_id: _, amount} = loan;
    assert!(coin::value(&coin) >= amount, EInsufficientAmount);

    let coin_balance = coin::into_balance(coin);
    balance::join(&mut pool.base, coin_balance);
}
```

