TITLE: Deserializing an Address from BCS Bytes in Move
DESCRIPTION: Extracts an address value from BCS-serialized bytes. It checks that enough bytes are available before attempting to read the address length bytes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/bcs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun peel_address(bcs: &mut BCS): address {
    assert!(bcs.bytes.length() >= address::length(), EOutOfRange);
    let (mut addr_bytes, mut i) = (vector[], 0);
    while (i < address::length()) {
        addr_bytes.push_back(bcs.bytes.pop_back());
        i = i + 1;
    };
    address::from_bytes(addr_bytes)
}
```

