TITLE: Partitioning Vector Elements in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This macro function splits a vector into two vectors based on a predicate function, returning a tuple of vectors for elements that satisfy and don't satisfy the predicate.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
public macro fun partition<$T>($v: vector<$T>, $f: |&$T| -> bool): (vector<$T>, vector<$T>) {
    let v = $v;
    let mut r1 = vector[];
    let mut r2 = vector[];
    v.do!(|e| if ($f(&e)) r1.push_back(e) else r2.push_back(e));
    (r1, r2)
}
```

