TITLE: Implementing Custom Receive Rule for EarmarkedPayment in Move
DESCRIPTION: A custom receive function that enforces authorization rules when an EarmarkedPayment is transferred. It verifies that the transaction sender matches the designated recipient address before releasing the payment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/examples/move/transfer-to-object/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun receive(
    parent: &mut UID,
    ticket: Receiving<EarmarkedPayment>,
    ctx: &TxContext
): IdentifiedPayment {
    let EarmarkedPayment { id, payment, for } = transfer::receive(parent, ticket);
    // If the sender isn't the address we specified, the transaction will abort.
    assert!(tx_context::sender(ctx) == for, ENotEarmarkedForSender);
    object::delete(id);
    payment
}
```

