TITLE: Mapping Vector Elements by Reference to New Vector in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This macro function creates a new vector by applying a function to each element of the input vector by reference, preserving the order of elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
public macro fun map_ref<$T, $U>($v: &vector<$T>, $f: |&$T| -> $U): vector<$U> {
    let v = $v;
    let mut r = vector[];
    v.do_ref!(|e| r.push_back($f(e)));
    r
}
```

