TITLE: Unstaking DEEP Tokens from DeepBook Pool
DESCRIPTION: Function for unstaking all DEEP tokens from a DeepBook pool. Unstaking removes both active and inactive stake, cancels any votes, forfeits maker rebates, and disables taker fee reductions for the remaining epoch. Unstaked tokens are immediately transferred back to the balance_manager.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/standards/deepbookv3/staking-governance.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun unstake(
    self: &mut Pool,
    balance_manager: &mut BalanceManager,
    ctx: &mut TxContext
) {
    let pool_id = object::id(self);
    let staking_record = begin_with_mut(&mut balance_manager.staking_records, pool_id);
    let active_stake = staking_record.active_stake;
    let inactive_stake = staking_record.inactive_stake;
    staking_record.active_stake = 0;
    staking_record.inactive_stake = 0;
    // If the user is voting on a proposal, remove the vote
    if (staking_record.proposal_voted_for != option::none()) {
        let proposal_id = *option::borrow(&staking_record.proposal_voted_for);
        let proposals = &mut self.proposals;
        if (table::contains(proposals, proposal_id)) {
            let proposal = table::borrow_mut(proposals, proposal_id);
            proposal.vote_count = proposal.vote_count - active_stake;
        };
        option::extract(&mut staking_record.proposal_voted_for);
    };
    let added_coin = balance::increase_supply(&mut self.deep_supply, active_stake + inactive_stake);
    balance::join(&mut balance_manager.balance, added_coin);
    self.unstaked = self.unstaked - active_stake - inactive_stake;
}
```

