TITLE: Is Primitive Type Check Function in Move
DESCRIPTION: Function that checks if a TypeName represents a primitive type (u8, u16, u32, u64, u128, u256, bool, address, vector).
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/type_name.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun is_primitive(self: &TypeName): bool {
    let bytes = self.name.as_bytes();
    bytes == &b"bool" ||
        bytes == &b"u8" ||
        bytes == &b"u16" ||
        bytes == &b"u32" ||
        bytes == &b"u64" ||
        bytes == &b"u128" ||
        bytes == &b"u256" ||
        bytes == &b"address" ||
        (
            bytes.length() >= 6 &&
            bytes[0] == ASCII_V &&
            bytes[1] == ASCII_E &&
            bytes[2] == ASCII_C &&
            bytes[3] == ASCII_T &&
            bytes[4] == ASCII_O &&
            bytes[5] == ASCII_R,
        )
}
```

