TITLE: Initializing a BitVector in Move
DESCRIPTION: Creates a new BitVector with the specified length. The function asserts that the length is greater than 0 and less than MAX_SIZE, then initializes all bits to false (0).
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/bit_vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun new(length: u64): BitVector {
    assert!(length > 0, ELENGTH);
    assert!(length < MAX_SIZE, ELENGTH);
    let mut counter = 0;
    let mut bit_field = vector::empty();
    while (counter < length) {
        bit_field.push_back(false);
        counter = counter + 1;
    };
    BitVector {
        length,
        bit_field,
    }
}
```

