TITLE: Implementing Generic Number Peeling Macro in Move
DESCRIPTION: A generic macro function for peeling numeric values from BCS-serialized bytes. Handles different integer sizes by taking length and bits parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/bcs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
macro fun peel_num<$I, $T>($bcs: &mut BCS, $len: u64, $bits: $I): $T {
    let bcs = $bcs;
    assert!(bcs.bytes.length() >= $len, EOutOfRange);
    let mut value: $T = 0;
    let mut i: $I = 0;
    let bits = $bits;
    while (i < bits) {
        let byte = bcs.bytes.pop_back() as $T;
        value = value + (byte << (i as u8));
        i = i + 8;
    };
    value
}
```

