TITLE: Adding Fixed-Point Numbers (uq_add)
DESCRIPTION: Adds two fixed-point numbers, checking for overflow. The result is cast back to the original type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/macros.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public macro fun uq_add<$T, $U>($a: $T, $b: $T, $max_t: $T, $abort_overflow: _): $T {
    let sum = $a as $U + ($b as $U);
    if (sum > $max_t as $U) $abort_overflow;
    sum as $T
}
```

