TITLE: Finding Optional Element Index in VecSet
DESCRIPTION: A function that searches for a key in a VecSet and returns its index as an Option. Returns None if the key is not found. Elements are checked in insertion order, not sorted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/vec_set.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
fun get_idx_opt<K: copy + drop>(self: &VecSet<K>, key: &K): Option<u64> {
    let mut i = 0;
    let n = size(self);
    while (i < n) {
        if (&self.contents[i] == key) {
            return option::some(i)
        };
        i = i + 1;
    };
    option::none()
}
```

