TITLE: Creating Custom Hook for Getting Reviews - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: The useGetReviews custom hook fetches and manages the state of reviews for a specific service. It exposes key information such as the service name and a list of reviews to be displayed. Requires TypeScript environment and React.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/guides/developer/app-examples/reviews-rating.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

const useGetReviews = (serviceId) => {
    const [reviews, setReviews] = useState([]);

    useEffect(() => {
        // Fetch reviews from API
        fetch(`/api/reviews/${serviceId}`)
            .then(response => response.json())
            .then(data => setReviews(data));
    }, [serviceId]);

    return reviews;
};
```

