TITLE: Calculating Single Depth at Tick Price (Move)
DESCRIPTION: Internal function to retrieve the depth of orders at a single tick price. Takes open orders, price, and timestamp as inputs. Returns the total quantity of valid orders at the given price.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/deepbook/clob.md#2025-04-22_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
fun get_level2_book_status(
    open_orders: &CritbitTree<TickLevel>,
    price: u64,
    time_stamp: u64
): u64 {
    let tick_level = critbit::borrow_leaf_by_key(open_orders, price);
    let tick_open_orders = &tick_level.open_orders;
    let mut depth = 0;
    let mut order_id = linked_table::front(tick_open_orders);
    let mut order: &Order;
    while (!option::is_none(order_id)) {
        order = linked_table::borrow(tick_open_orders, *option::borrow(order_id));
        if (order.expire_timestamp > time_stamp) depth = depth + order.quantity;
        order_id = linked_table::next(tick_open_orders, *option::borrow(order_id));
    };
    depth
}
```

