TITLE: Vector Partition Macro Implementation in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Splits a vector into two vectors based on a predicate function, separating elements into matching and non-matching groups.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
public macro fun partition<$T>($v: vector<$T>, $f: |&$T| -> bool): (vector<$T>, vector<$T>) {
    let v = $v;
    let mut r1 = vector[];
    let mut r2 = vector[];
    v.do!(|e| if ($f(&e)) r1.push_back(e) else r2.push_back(e));
    (r1, r2)
}
```

