TITLE: Checking Address in Per Type List - Move
DESCRIPTION: The `v1_per_type_list_contains` function checks if an address is present in the denied addresses of a specific type. It also checks the denied count to determine if the address is truly denied.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/sui/deny_list.md#2025-04-22_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
fun v1_per_type_list_contains(list: &sui::deny_list::PerTypeList, type: vector<u8>, addr: address): bool {
    if (!list.denied_count.contains(addr)) return false;
    let denied_count = &list.denied_count[addr];
    if (*denied_count == 0) return false;
    if (!list.denied_addresses.contains(type)) return false;
    let denied_addresses = &list.denied_addresses[type];
    denied_addresses.contains(&addr)
}
```

