TITLE: Mutably Borrowing an Item from a Kiosk using PTB
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to mutably borrow an item from a Sui Kiosk using Programmable Transaction Blocks. It uses the 'borrow_val' and 'return_val' functions from the 'kiosk' module to take an asset, potentially modify it, and place it back in the same transaction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/standards/kiosk.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let tx = new Transaction();

let itemType = 'ITEM_TYPE';
let itemId = tx.pure.id('<ITEM_ID>');
let kioskArg = tx.object('<ID>');
let capArg = tx.object('<ID>');

let [item, promise] = tx.moveCall({
	target: '0x2::kiosk::borrow_val',
	arguments: [kioskArg, capArg, itemId],
	typeArguments: [itemType],
});

// freely mutate or reference the `item`
// any calls are available as long as they take a reference
// `returnValue` must be explicitly called

tx.moveCall({
	target: '0x2::kiosk::return_val',
	arguments: [kioskArg, item, promise],
	typeArguments: [itemType],
});
```

