TITLE: Processing References to Paired Elements in Sui Move
DESCRIPTION: A macro function that iterates through two vectors and applies a function to references of each pair of elements. The vectors are not modified, and it aborts if they have different lengths.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: Sui Move
CODE:
```
public macro fun zip_do_ref<$T1, $T2, $R: drop>(
    $v1: &vector<$T1>,
    $v2: &vector<$T2>,
    $f: |&$T1, &$T2| -> $R,
) {
    let v1 = $v1;
    let v2 = $v2;
    let len = v1.length();
    assert!(len == v2.length());
    len.do!(|i| $f(&v1[i], &v2[i]));
}
```

