TITLE: Shifting BitVector Left
DESCRIPTION: Shifts the bits in the BitVector to the left by the specified amount. If the amount is greater than or equal to the vector's length, all bits are set to false (0).
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/bit_vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun shift_left(bitvector: &mut BitVector, amount: u64) {
    if (amount >= bitvector.length) {
        let len = bitvector.bit_field.length();
        let mut i = 0;
        while (i < len) {
            let elem = &mut bitvector.bit_field[i];
            *elem = false;
            i = i + 1;
        };
    } else {
        let mut i = amount;
        while (i < bitvector.length) {
            if (bitvector.is_index_set(i)) bitvector.set(i - amount)
            else bitvector.unset(i - amount);
            i = i + 1;
        };
        i = bitvector.length - amount;
        while (i < bitvector.length) {
            unset(bitvector, i);
            i = i + 1;
        };
    }
}
```

