TITLE: Filtering Vector Elements in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This macro function creates a new vector containing only the elements of the input vector that satisfy a given predicate function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
public macro fun filter<$T: drop>($v: vector<$T>, $f: |&$T| -> bool): vector<$T> {
    let v = $v;
    let mut r = vector[];
    v.do!(|e| if ($f(&e)) r.push_back(e));
    r
}
```

