TITLE: Executing Closure on Option Value in Sui Move
DESCRIPTION: The 'do' macro function destroys an Option<T> and calls the provided closure on the inner value if it exists. It takes an Option<T> and a closure as parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/option.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: Sui Move
CODE:
```
public macro fun do<$T, $R: drop>($o: Option<$T>, $f: |$T| -> $R) {
    let o = $o;
    if (o.is_some()) { $f(o.destroy_some()); }
    else o.destroy_none()
}
```

