TITLE: Claiming Rebates in DeepBook Pool
DESCRIPTION: Function for claiming accumulated rewards in a DeepBook pool. The balance_manager must have rewards available to claim. Upon successful execution, the balance_manager is updated with the claimed rewards and the rebate accounting is reset.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/docs/content/standards/deepbookv3/staking-governance.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
public fun claim_rebates(
    self: &mut Pool,
    balance_manager: &mut BalanceManager,
    ctx: &mut TxContext
) {
    let pool_id = object::id(self);
    let staking_record = begin_with_mut(&mut balance_manager.staking_records, pool_id);
    let rebate = staking_record.accumulated_trading_rebate;
    assert!(rebate > 0, EInsufficientRebate);
    staking_record.accumulated_trading_rebate = 0;
    let added_coin = coin::take(&mut self.rebate_coin, rebate, ctx);
    coin::put(&mut balance_manager.coin, added_coin);
}
```

