TITLE: Invalid Complex Recursive Generic Function Calls in Move
DESCRIPTION: Shows a more complex example of invalid recursive generic function calls in Move that could create infinitely many types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/documentation/book/src/generics.md#2025-04-22_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
module a::n {
    public struct A<T> {}

    // Infinitely many types -- NOT allowed.
    // error!
    // foo<T1, T2> -> bar<T2, T1> -> foo<T2, A<T1>>
    //   -> bar<A<T1>, T2> -> foo<A<T1>, A<T2>>
    //   -> bar<A<T2>, A<T1>> -> foo<A<T2>, A<A<T1>>>
    //   -> ...
    fun foo<T1, T2>() {
        bar<T2, T1>();
    }

    fun bar<T1, T2> {
        foo<T1, A<T2>>();
    }
}
```

