TITLE: Dividing U64 by FixedPoint32
DESCRIPTION: Divides a u64 integer by a fixed-point number, handling the scale conversion and checking for division by zero and overflow conditions. The result is truncated to remove any fractional part.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/fixed_point32.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun divide_u64(val: u64, divisor: FixedPoint32): u64 {
    // Check for division by zero.
    assert!(divisor.value != 0, EDIVISION_BY_ZERO);
    // First convert to 128 bits and then shift left to
    // add 32 fractional zero bits to the dividend.
    let scaled_value = val as u128 << 32;
    let quotient = scaled_value / (divisor.value as u128);
    // Check whether the value is too large.
    assert!(quotient <= MAX_U64, EDIVISION);
    // the value may be too large, which will cause the cast to fail
    // with an arithmetic error.
    quotient as u64
}
```

