TITLE: Creating a New BitVector in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Implements the new function to create a BitVector with a specified length. It validates the length and initializes the bit field with false values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-framework/docs/std/bit_vector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
public fun new(length: u64): BitVector {
    assert!(length > 0, ELENGTH);
    assert!(length < MAX_SIZE, ELENGTH);
    let mut counter = 0;
    let mut bit_field = vector::empty();
    while (counter < length) {
        bit_field.push_back(false);
        counter = counter + 1;
    };
    BitVector {
        length,
        bit_field,
    }
}
```

