TITLE: ASCII String Creation and Validation - Move
DESCRIPTION: Functions to create ASCII strings with validation from byte vectors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/external-crates/move/crates/move-stdlib/docs/std/ascii.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Move
CODE:
```
public fun string(bytes: vector<u8>): String {
    let x = try_string(bytes);
    assert!(x.is_some(), EInvalidASCIICharacter);
    x.destroy_some()
}

public fun try_string(bytes: vector<u8>): Option<String> {
    let is_valid = bytes.all!(|byte| is_valid_char(*byte));
    if (is_valid) option::some(String { bytes })
    else option::none()
}
```

