TITLE: Setting up environment variables for Postgres
DESCRIPTION: These commands set environment variables required for Postgresql. LDFLAGS and CPPFLAGS specify the location of libraries and include files, while PATH adds the Postgresql binaries to the system's executable search path. This allows other tools to find and use Postgresql.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/sui/blob/main/crates/sui-indexer/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
